et subsumed by the streaming economy. Maria San Filippo explores how filmmaker and film render a singular voice and story that queers not only its celebrated romcom predecessors but also the gay coming-out film and the lesbian romance alike. The book concludes with an interview with Akhavan.San Filippo pays special tribute to Akhavan’s audacious sensibility and the “inbetweener” moxie that makes Appropriate Behavior an unparalleled portrayal of bisexuality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBisexuality in motion pictures. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican cinema.  aAnnie Hall.  aBIPOC filmmaker.  aBrooklyn.  aDesiree Akhavan.  aIranian American.  aLGBTQ cinema.  aLGBTQ film.  aLGBTQ.  aLena Dunham.  aMillennials.  aPark Slope.  aPersian.  aSundance.  aWoody Allen.  aauteur.  abisexual.  acomedy.  acoming out.  adiasporic cinema.  afemale filmmaker.  afeminist.  agay cinema.  agay film.  agay.  ainbetween.  aindependent.  aindie TV.  aindie cinema.  aindie film.  aindie filmmaker.  aindie.  alesbian cinema.  alesbian.  aqueer cinema.  aqueer film.  aqueer.  aromance.  aromantic comedy.  aromcom.  asexuality.  athreesome.  auncoupling.  aweb series.  awoman director.  awoman filmmaker.  awoman of color.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801568040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228015680423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228015680/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-al